testlink.api.java.client.tc.autoexec
Interface TestCase

All Known Implementing Classes:
ExecutableTestCase
public interface TestCase

The TestCase interface is used to hold the data from an existing TestCase that is acquired using the TestLink API or for creating a new Test Case in the TestLink database. Therefore, the interface provides to initialization procedures. initExistingCase() and and initNewCase(). The auto executor will expect all the data about the test case to be initialized by one of these two methods.

Author:
Daniel Padilla
